<img src=http://www.dimensional.com/~malekith/sigfiles/erylyingyang.jpg border=0></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#AADDDD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utheskyfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Skyfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/01 4:20:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who deserves Ragefire?  The thoughts of a casual player.</span><hr size=1> If anyone were to come up with a system that was truly fair by favoring those who put the most time in for their epic first and others later, and at the same time make clerics lives easier, I would be all for it.  I have yet to hear of such a system and no cleric has come forward with an answer.  All I hear is a lot of bitchin from clerics who want to feel a little more special and a little more useful than other clerics, yet aren't willing or able to put the time in to get the epic that grants them that.<br>
<br>
At first I felt sorry for clerics.  Then they kept complaining while offering no real solutions.  So I tried to councel them a little bit.  Then more complaining, less real solution offering.  Then I let them deal with their own affairs.  Now I'm at the point where I'm losing a little bit of my faith in humanity as so many different clerics time and time again say there should be a list only to repeatedly, and indefinately fail, abysmally, again and again and again, to offer a solution that doesn't screw everyone over who IS willing to put in the hours versus people who AREN'T willing.<br>
<br>
If this was such a major problem then I would imagine that someone would have taken the time to establish a working system to eliminate this problem.  Right?  Guess it's not as serious a problem as people think it is then.  Because you'd think with all the clerics at the zordak point, at least ONE would have come up with a working idea right?  Nope.  Guess not... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utheskyfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Skyfyre</A> at: 8/1/01 4:21:03 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DDDDAA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uididartzan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ididar Tzan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/01 6:30:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who deserves Ragefire?  The thoughts of a casual player.</span><hr size=1> To answer your question, you silly dorf ....<br>
<br>
Its because that's how the game is designed. You get the stuff if you put in the time. As a player we all start this game out with nothing but the grey matter between our ears (except ebay types) and we work our way up from that. What we get is because we have friends who got something for us or because we plunked our asses down or ran around the gameworld to get something. But, ultimately, it never comes free. Either you put in the time playing and making friends who give you stuff or you put in the time camping it yourself. You paid some price for it and it didn't involve JUST killing the mob when your name was called.<br>
<br>
Basically, you paid your dues.<br>
<br>
You did what everyone before you did and you did what everyone who comes after you should do, put in the time if you want the item.<br>
<br>
Afterall, if this game was more about having an itchy trigger finger or having good hand-eye coordination we wouldn't be here saying that Verant should tweak the game for those who don't have good hand-eye coordination, would we? But, because their game involves TIME some of us insist they should either change the spawn times or we, as players, should setup lists to allow more people access to an item. Well, imo, that defeats the purpose of the game. Helping friends camp something is one thing ... because that person has put in the time making friends who're willing to make that sacrifice. But, setting up a nice little comfortable list isn't about making friends, its about making it relatively easy on the casual player who would normally never see their epic. They'd normally never see it because of time just like the player with the bad hand-eye coordination would never see his epic in a game more geared towards that. In the case of the other game we couldn't do anything to help them but, at the same time, I seriously doubt we'd be caring that much because most people seem more willing to accept a limitation such as superior hand-eye coordination moreso than they're willing to accept a limitation of time. <p><a href=http://www.3deearts.com/sos/profile.asp?who=Fdor><img src=http://home.thezone.net/~dhill/Fdor-Sig.jpg></href></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#AADDDD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usergex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sergex </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/01 8:06:57 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~haujobb/images/BMage01L.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who deserves Ragefire?  The thoughts of a casual player.</span><hr size=1> I agree with Idiadar that this is how the game trains you to play.  We are indoctrinated from the time we want to get Bronze Armor that in order to get what you want you must sit and wait for it to drop.  If you want to change the way the game is played only for Ragefire, it's not going to happen.  <br>
