Infinitus Vindicat</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DDDDAA><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upetralifeline.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Petra Lifeline</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/01 8:36:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who deserves Ragefire?  The thoughts of a casual player.</span><hr size=1> I remember seeing a post from Verant once upon a time that stated &quot;Epics are not for the casual gamer. Epics are for our 24/7/365 players out there. Epics are not for everyone.&quot;<br>
<br>
Being the second newest cleric on Prexus (Gratz to Adalyyn for getting hers last nite!) to recieve my rez stick, I can say, lists are crap. I wont even start there. It truly does take away from the &quot;epic encounter&quot; and turn it into a &quot;every cleric deserves&quot; which is BS.<br>
<br>
Verant put this bottle neck here just like there is one in every epic quest. VSR for rangers and druids, Vox and Naggy for palidans, Big green dragon for warriors, all dragons for bards...see what im getting at here? Imagine being a palidan and not wanting to level past 52 just so you can continue to go on Vox/Naggy raids with hopes of getting the books.<br>
<br>
Does every cleric who is of sufficient level and have his/her pearl deserve Zordak? No. Does every player in the game deserve his/her epic? No. Would I like to see every player with his/her epic/rez stick? Definately yes. BUT, I cant stand to see a list. The way I see it, if you want your epic, no matter of class, you need to do the time. If you dont have the patience to sit there and wait for a spawn, be that behind one or two other people, how can you say you truly want your epic?<br>
<br>
The list. The list that was being created in SolB was total crap. That was one of the reasons I did my epic when I did. I happened to be off for 4 days, and Im not one to follow a list when the person isnt sitting there camping. So I got in line, and I have mine now. A list out here...how could it possibly be made fair? If you try to tell me that it is more fair for a level 52 cleric who cant even cast the frigging spell from his/her spell book to be in line in front of a level 60 who has done his/her time in EQ, thats a bunch of shiat. How would you make it fair to those that are sitting there already? I dont know why a cleric would even want a list. It is such a sence of accomplishment by being there, waiting, clearing the FG's, waiting some more, and finally, having a ranger/druid out of no where say &quot;Hes up!&quot;. After waiting for 96 hours for my spawn, my heart was racing when I heard this. It stayed that way for a good 6 hours after I already had my epic in hand. Wow Im rambling, lemme end this.<br>
<br>
1. Should every cleric get their epic? Probably not.<br>
<br>
2. Should there be a list? Definately not.<br>
<br>
3. Should every cleric that wants it get in line in SolB camping it right along with every other cleric there? Definately yes.<br>
<br>
Just my 1cp<br>
<br>
